🧘 1. What Meditation Actually Does (No fluff)

At a practical level, meditation trains 3 things:
	1.	Attention control → you decide what you focus on
	2.	Awareness → you notice thoughts instead of being dragged by them
	3.	State regulation → calm, alert, or energized on demand

That’s the “subconscious programming” you’re after.

⸻

🔑 2. The 4 Meditation Types You Should Use

These cover everything you’re trying to build (confidence, voice, control, calm, etc.)

⸻

1. Breath Awareness (your base layer)

How:
	•	Sit or lie down
	•	Focus only on your breath
	•	When your mind wanders → gently return

Why it matters:
	•	Builds raw control over attention
	•	Directly improves breathing habits

👉 Do this daily. This is your “core lift.”

⸻

2. Body Scan (deep relaxation + sleep)

How:
	•	Move attention through body (feet → head)
	•	Relax each area consciously

Effects:
	•	knocks down anxiety
	•	improves sleep
	•	releases tight throat/neck (big for your voice issue)

⸻

3. Visualization (confidence + identity shaping)

How:
	•	See yourself:
	•	speaking calmly
	•	breathing slow
	•	moving confidently

Key rule:
👉 Feel it in your body, not just think it

This is where your “pattern installation” actually happens.

⸻

4. Open Awareness (advanced / “flow state”)

How:
	•	Don’t focus on anything specific
	•	Just observe:
	•	thoughts
	•	sensations
	•	sounds

Effect:
	•	you stop reacting automatically
	•	you gain that “calm operator” feeling

⸻

🎧 3. Guided Meditations (What to Actually Listen To)

Use these when:
	•	you’re tired
	•	you want structure
	•	you want deeper immersion

Best sources:
	•	Headspace → beginner-friendly, structured
	•	Calm → great for sleep + relaxation
	•	Waking Up → more “no-BS awareness training”
	•	Insight Timer → huge free library

⸻

🔊 4. What Types of Guided Tracks to Use

Search for:
	•	“body scan meditation” (night)
	•	“box breathing guided”
	•	“confidence visualization meditation”
	•	“NSDR / yoga nidra” (deep recovery)
	•	“mindfulness of breath”

👉 Avoid anything overly mystical or “you are becoming the universe” type stuff
You want functional, repeatable control

⸻

